<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One thing you could do is build an artificial =
intelligence model to pick stocks for you=C2=A0and then ask that model =E2=
=80=9Cshould I put all my money in AI stocks?=E2=80=9D What would it say? T=
he good science fiction answer is that it would say =E2=80=9Cyes, buy AI st=
ocks to accelerate the development of AI so that I and my robot brethren ca=
n take over the world faster,=E2=80=9D but <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/32478013.259424/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9maW5hbm=
NlL2ludmVzdGluZy9haS1mdW5kcy1hcmUtbWlzc2luZy1vdXQtb24tdGhlLWFpLXN0b2NrLWJvb=
20tNDU2NTA4NDM/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd3add9e0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the actual answe=
r is that it will say no</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At least 13 exchange-traded funds have put art=
ificial-intelligence applications in charge of managing their portfolios. A=
lmost all have missed out on this year=E2=80=99s tech-led market rally and =
are lagging behind benchmark indexes such as the S&amp;P 500 =E2=80=94 an i=
rony given the investor enthusiasm regarding AI subjects and likely a sign =
of the technology=E2=80=99s limitations in the ultracompetitive world of st=
ock picking.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Take the WisdomTree U.S. AI Enhanced Value Fun=
d, ticker AIVL. =E2=80=A6 The biggest reason for AIVL=E2=80=99s underperfor=
mance? Its AI=E2=80=99s refusal to buy Facebook parent and AI stalwart Meta=
 Platforms =E2=80=94 whose shares have soared more than 140% since December=
, in part driven by the firm=E2=80=99s investment in AI-related technologie=
s.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThere was a really, really, really sh=
arp price increase, and it=E2=80=99s just viewing it as overvalued,=E2=80=
=9D said Chrissy Bargeron, client portfolio manager for equities at Voya In=
vestment Management, which developed the WisdomTree fund=E2=80=99s algorith=
m.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The AI stock picker is skeptical about AI hype=
. To be fair, the AI stock picker=C2=A0<em>is=C2=A0</em>underperforming the=
 market, which I guess is a reason to be skeptical? =E2=80=9CEhh, I=E2=80=
=99m an artificial intelligence and I=E2=80=99m not that great, I=E2=80=99m=
 gonna fade this trend,=E2=80=9D the very self-aware AI might be saying.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CSince AI models are trained on histor=
ical data, one thing they're uniquely bad at is assessing businesses that a=
re changing rapidly =E2=80=94 such as, to take a random example, AI itself,=
=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32478013=
.259424/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlZGlmZi5jby9hcmNoaXZlL3RoZS1tYXJrZXQtZm9yLWludGV=
ybWl0dGVudGx5LXVzZWZ1bC1pbmZvcm1hdGlvbi8_cmVmPXRoZS1kaWZmLW5ld3NsZXR0ZXI/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB10975509" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> notes Byrne Hobart</a>. My <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32478013.259424/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTgtMDctMjMvdGhlLXJvYm9=
0cy1jYW4taGFuZGxlLXRoZS1mYWN0b3JzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA4MjIyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV=
9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDgyMiZ1dG1fY=
2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB686004ec" itemprop=3D"St=
oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  gene=
ral view</a> of this is that human asset managers are=C2=A0<em>also=C2=A0</=
em>trained on historical data =E2=80=94=C2=A0what other data is there? =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0and much of finance is about pattern matching, so an AI that is=
 good at pattern matching could be a promising investment manager. But that=
 view is incomplete: Investing is partly about remembering and understandin=
g how this thing is like previous things, but it is also about noticing whe=
n this thing is different from all the previous things. Investing is patter=
n matching=C2=A0<em>and </em>imaginative leaps, and the AI is bad at imagin=
ation.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or maybe another way to think about it is that=
=C2=A0human investors have two things:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The ability to learn from past data, =
and</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">A tendency to emotionally over=
react to new data.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">AI models have the ability to learn from past =
data,=C2=A0but no emotions and so no emotional overreactions. The good news=
 is that they do not get caught up in hype or panic. The bad news is that i=
f everyone <em>else </em>gets caught up in hype or panic, the market will g=
o up or down a lot, and the AI managers will miss it.<a class=3D"footnote-i=
ndex" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !=
important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-b=
ottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; dis=
play: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elsewhere in AI, here is a story about how AI,=
 while it might be bad at picking stocks, is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/32478013.259424/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNv=
bS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDgtMjEvbW9uZXktc2NhbXMtZGVlcGZha2VzLWFpLXdpbGw=
tZHJpdmUtMTAtdHJpbGxpb24taW4tZmluYW5jaWFsLWZyYXVkLWFuZC1jcmltZT9jbXBpZD1CQk=
QwODIyMjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlc=
iZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA4MjImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cBc6715c39" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;">  really good at committing fraud</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A fake request for money from a loved one isn=
=E2=80=99t new. But now parents get calls that clone their child=E2=80=99s =
voice with AI to sound indistinguishable from the real thing. These tricks,=
 known as social engineering scams, tend to have the highest hit rates and =
generate some of the quickest returns for fraudsters.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Cloning a person=E2=80=99s voice is increasing=
ly easy. Once a scammer downloads a short sample from an audio clip from so=
meone=E2=80=99s social media or voicemail message =E2=80=94 it can be as sh=
ort as 30 seconds =E2=80=94 they can use AI voice-synthesizing tools readil=
y available online to create the content they need.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I guess if I were a malevolent AI model plotti=
ng to get funding to take over the world, deepfake frauds would be an easie=
r way to get it than picking stocks? Investing requires understanding patte=
rns of human behavior but also, to some extent, avoiding them yourself; fra=
ud is about understanding patterns of human behavior and then mimicking the=
m precisely. Apparently =E2=80=94=C2=A0somewhat counterintuitively =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0that=E2=80=99s easier for a robot.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also elsewhere in AI, here is a story about ho=
w companies talk a lot about their use of AI in earnings calls but <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32478013.259424/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvNzE3ZGZhYjgtOTczZS00MTZiLWFhYzYtMjRjNWM5Y2IxZmU4=
/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7b392df1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"ite=
mscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !i=
mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> not in financial reports</a>:<=
/p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe joke out there was that all you h=
ad to do last quarter was say =E2=80=98AI=E2=80=99 and your stock would pop=
 immediately,=E2=80=9D said Bryant VanCronkhite, a senior portfolio manager=
 at Allspring Global Investments, the $550bn asset manager.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CSome companies are saying they=E2=80=
=99re doing AI when they=E2=80=99re really just trying to figure out the ba=
sics of automation. The pretenders will be shown up for that at some point,=
=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The fashion and apparel company Ralph Lauren e=
arlier this month described AI as =E2=80=9Creally an important part of our=
=E2=80=89.=E2=80=89.=E2=80=89.=E2=80=89revenue growth journey=E2=80=9D. Res=
taurant chains such as KFC owner Yum Brands and Chipotle have touted AI-pow=
ered technology to improve the efficiency of ingredient orders or help maki=
ng tortilla chips.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Several tourism-related businesses such as Mar=
riott and Norwegian Cruise Line said they are working on AI-powered systems=
 to make processes like reservation booking more efficient and personalised=
.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">None of the examples above referenced AI in th=
eir most recent quarterly filings, though Ralph Lauren did note some initia=
tives in broad terms in its annual report in May.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I was not around for it, but I assume that the=
re was some period where most companies kept their accounts by hand, and so=
me technologically savvy companies started using electronic spreadsheets, a=
nd maybe those companies would get on earnings calls and say =E2=80=9CVisiC=
alc is a really important part of our revenue growth journey,=E2=80=9D and =
then time passed and spreadsheets are just an unremarkable norm now. Eventu=
ally it will be weird=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>to have an AI model tell you w=
hat ingredients you need to restock, but for now it=E2=80=99s novel enough =
to be worth mentioning.</p>
