<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">How is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/32478013.259424/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYWxjaGVteS5jb20vb3ZlcnZpZ=
XdzL25mdC1zZWxsZXItZmluYW5jaW5n/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB903c4ea6" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 the market for non-fungible tokens going</a>?</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">NiftyApes, an NFT lending protocol backed by C=
oinbase and Variant, is the first to bring Seller Financing to the world of=
 NFTs. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The seller lists an item for sale on an NFT ma=
rketplace that has integrated the NiftyApes SDK and sets financing options =
(either custom or pre-made) including price, down payment, duration, and in=
terest rate. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The NFT is transferred to a neutral NFT seller=
 financing escrow smart contract which has been audited by Quantstamp and S=
herlock ensuring a secure transaction. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Immediately after clicking =E2=80=9CBuy,=E2=80=
=9D the buyer becomes the delegated owner of the NFT and can start using it=
. =E2=80=A6=C2=A0=C2=A0Such use cases include giving the buyer immediate ac=
cess to token gated Discords, airdrops, and more. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The buyer makes payments until the purchase is=
 paid in full. Once the seller financed purchase is fully paid, the NFT own=
ership is transferred out of the escrow contract to the buyer's wallet.=C2=
=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If the buyer fails to make a payment, the sell=
er keeps all the payments made and can reclaim the NFT to sell again.=C2=A0=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A buyer initiates the purchase by making a dow=
n payment on the NFT and agreeing to the payment terms set by the seller.</=
p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">To be fair, seller financing is coming back in=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32478013.259424/a=
HR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9zZWxsZXItZmluYW5jaW5nLXRvLWF2b2lkLWhp=
Z2gtbW9ydGdhZ2UtcmF0ZXMtY2Q5M2Q3MDU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB95e9a8c6" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #cc=
c;"> the housing market too</a>. The basic story is the same: There was che=
ap and abundant credit to buy big illiquid durable assets (houses, JPEGs of=
 monkeys); people bought them and bid up their prices; credit dried up; now=
 the owners want to sell but the buyers can=E2=80=99t borrow money to buy; =
the obvious solution is for the sellers to lend the buyers the money. I jus=
t love the idea that you=E2=80=99d need to buy a JPEG of a monkey on the in=
stallment plan.</p>
